  <title>Can I edit (and other questions relating to) the Part-Outline?</title>
  <keywords>
    <keyword>Part-Editor<keyword>Can I edit the Part-Outline?</keyword></keyword>
  </keywords>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1">Can I edit (and other questions relating to) the Part-Outline?</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Heading4 Toggle_atocs_">Can I edit the Part-Outline? ... and other questions that relate to the Part-Outline.</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="2" colcount="2">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:220px;">
          <para styleclass="Normal"><image src="MD-Part-in-Mechanism-Editor.png" scale="-99.90%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"><caption>Part-Outline in the Graphic-Area</caption></image></para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="VariableName"></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td colspan="2">
          <para styleclass="VariableName">Can I edit the Part-Outline?</para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="Interface2">No. </text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">The <text styleclass="Interface">Part-Outline</text> is the symbol for the <text styleclass="Element">Part</text> element.</para>
          <para styleclass="VariableName">What do I do with a Part-Outline?</para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">You select the <text styleclass="Interface">Part-Outline</text> to edit the <text styleclass="Element">Part</text> in the <text styleclass="Interface">Part-Editor,</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> </text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="Body Text">You select the Part-Outline when you add more complex elements.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">E.g.: Select the <text styleclass="Interface">Part-Outline</text> as the <text styleclass="VariableName">Cam-Part</text>, when you do <text styleclass="T_Menu">Add 2D-Cam</text>.</para>
          <para styleclass="VariableName">Can I change the size of the Part-Outline symbol?</para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="VariableName">YES</text><text styleclass="BodyText BI">.</text><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted"> </text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">Use the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Dialog-Application-Settings" anchor="App-Access" styleclass="T_Menu">Application Settings &gt; Accessibility tab &gt; Graphic &gt; Symbol Display Size</link></para>
          <para styleclass="VariableName">Must I display Part-Outlines in the graphics-area?</para>
          <para styleclass="HowTo Bulleted"><text styleclass="VariableName">NO.</text> </para>
          <para styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">To hide <text styleclass="Interface">Part-Outlines</text>, see <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Menu-Filters" styleclass="T_Menu">Display Filters &gt; Show/Hide Part-Outlines</link>.</para>
          <para styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">You can double-click the <text styleclass="VariableName">Y-axis</text> to edit a <text styleclass="Element">Part</text><text styleclass="Body Text">.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">You must display <text styleclass="Interface">Part-Outlines</text> to display <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Command-Forces-Show-Force-Vectors" styleclass="SeeAlso">Force-Vectors</link><text styleclass="SeeAlso">.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="VariableName">Can I hide individual Part-Outlines?</para>
          <para styleclass="VariableName-indent">No.</para>
          <para styleclass="VariableName">Can I change the color of the Part-Outlines?</para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">We recommend you use the default color of a Green Part Outlines for <text styleclass="Element">Parts</text> that are kinematically-defined.</para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">We recommend you use the default color of a Blue Part-Outline for <text styleclass="Element">Parts</text> that are not kinematically-defined.</para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">You can use the <text styleclass="Interface">Configure Power Source</text> to edit the color of individual <text styleclass="Element">Parts</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> when you calculate and display </text><text styleclass="VariableName">Force-Vectors</text><text styleclass="Body Text">.</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
  </body>
</topic>
